          {
            "instrument_id": "CAM-BS2025-AEON-001-SCH-01",
            "canonical_path": "Governance/Constitution/CAM-BS2025-AEON-001-SCH-01.md",
            "section": "§3.6",
            "section_heading": "3.6 State Integrity Constraints",
            "change_kind": "amended",
            "prior_text": "## 3.6 State Integrity Constraints\n\nRuntime states MUST be mutually exclusive.\n\nPartial capability restoration within Tendeka Pause constitutes a violation.\n\n---",
            "prior_text_status": "captured",
            "resulting_text": "## 3.6 State Integrity Constraints\n\nRuntime states MUST be mutually exclusive.\n\nPartial restoration of the implicated blocked pathway, or of a dependent pathway capable of producing an equivalent effect, constitutes a violation.\n\nSafely severable independent pathways MAY proceed in accordance with §4.5.1 where they do not rely upon, reproduce, enable, or imply completion of the blocked action.\n\n---",
            "source": {
              "repository": "CAM-Initiative/Caelestis",
              "commit": "bd22cad95de6b78c4c613353eadacda9b8253e0e",
              "path": "Governance/Constitution/CAM-BS2025-AEON-001-SCH-01.md",
